we had summoner diversity in top lane once.

{{summoner:12}} {{summoner:14}} {{summoner:11}} 

guess what happened... this is bullshit. if they want diversity, then they shouldnt have nerfed lane smite, when it was on par with tp and ignite, just because they think smite doesnt belong into lane. it didnt cause any actual problems.

if they wanted summoner diversity, they would look into buffing {{summoner:1}} and changing {{summoner:4}} into a better balanced version of {{summoner:32}} for summoners rift.

make {{summoner:4}} an actual nieche summoner for champions that need the ability to engage and dont make it the all purpose escape/engage summoner.

if someone wants escape he should look for {{summoner:6}} {{summoner:7}} {{summoner:1}}

